18. Marsi memorem duelli‚l The Marsic or Social War continued from 13. c. 91 to 89. It was a rising of the Socii, the states of Italy, for the pur- pose of getting the Roman franchise. Tho Marsi took a prominent partin the war, which was sometimes called by their name. The Servile War lasted from B. o. 73 to 71. It was an outbreak of the slaves of Italy, who, under Spartacus, himself a slave and gladiator, were formed into a vast army, and traversed the whole country from Rhegium to the Po.
